sanger.math.set
Class NaturalDomain

java.lang.Object
  sanger.math.set.AbstractSet
      sanger.math.set.NaturalDomain
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Iterable<java.lang.Integer>
public class NaturalDomain
extends AbstractSet
implements java.lang.Iterable<java.lang.Integer>

A finite domain of natural numbers. A NaturalDomain is defined over a NaturalSpace and does not have to be continuous. Access to min, max, map, one, cardinality and last values can be concidered to be of O(1) complexity as they are internaly cached.

Author:
Lior Galanti
